Thoughts on Ask Yourself: Who is responsible for Product Development & Management?





 Lisbet Sherlock says: 

			August 5, 2013 at 1:55 pm 
Peter – interesting blog! We are also focussing on this dynamic as we start to think about the full implications of the internet of everything. Once your product has left the shelves, that used to be the end of the story. Now – if you can stay connected to your product through its lifecycle – you can turn it into a service, you can really understand how it is used, maybe you can even deliver further value added services on top. For some interesting examples, take a look at what Philips is doing with connected lighting and even the connected toothbrush.




